<plot>When 12-year-old Charlie Dodgson wins an essay writing contest he sees big dreams of someday becoming a writer. However, before his piece can be published, Charlie must be reviewed by "seasoned" editors who slowly chip away at the originality of his work. When finally faced with the decision of making the suggested changes, or risk having his award revoked and his story unpublished, Charlie learns the high cost of integrity.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?602507</url></doc>
